<!-- 
 1.suppose this service-content component is very heavy component 
 2.i want to exclude it from the initial bundle.
 3.once the initial bundle is downloaded and rendered in browser after that i want angular 
 to make another request to download a bundle for this services component .
 4. to achieve that we can use defer block after that we need to specify the trigger  and we wrap the content
 which we want to load lazily inside this block.
 this component will not be included in the initial bundle it is a deferred content it will be lazily loaded 
 now we need to specify when this component should be lazily loaded for that we need to specify trigger we use on and trigger name 
 
 default trigge -idle 

 1.Idle trigger -loads the bundle for the deferred content when the browser is idle  angular makes the request to downalod the bundle for the 
 deffered content it will wait for the browser    to run the styles and scripts in case of ideal
 2.Immediate trigger-very similar to idle trigger but the difference is that immediate trigger does not wait for the browser
 to be idle as soon as the initial bundle downlaoded angular will make the request to dowload the bundle for deffered content
 3.viewport trigger-loads the deferred content as soon as the block enters screen .
 placeholder is mandatory in case of view port 
 trigger 
 -->
<!-- 1.@defer(on idle)
2.@defer(on immediate)
3.@defer(on viewport)
@placeholder (minimum 2000){
} is mandatory
 4.@defer(on interaction()) -oninteraction
 5.@defer(on hover())  --onhover
 6.@defer(on timer(3000)) -on timer
 7.@defer(when show) -lazy load deferred content conditionally true only
 8.@defer(prefetch) -when the browser is idle it can prefetch the bundle but not 
 render in ui
 when the browser is idle it will lazy load the deffered content download the inital bundle  
 render in ui incase of idle 
 9.loading-after 500 ms only loading will be displayed when the bundle for deffered content is download
10.error -when the bundle for deffered content is failed or any network issues 
-->

@defer(on viewport){
<app-service-content></app-service-content>
}
<!-- this placeholder we can use for flickering  when browser is idle service component is lazyily loaded -->
@placeholder{
<p>Loading service component</p>
}
@loading(minimum 300;after 500){
<p>execute when the bundle for the component is downloaded if you want to show something in ui</p>
}
@error{
<p>an error occurred</p>
}
